B.aiC=new A.c("If you cannot drop your Pawn along the 6th file, check if you can on the 5th file. P*5b will also be a very effective move (Diagram 3-2).")
B.N4=new A.p("ln1g1R3/1ks1P4/pppp5/5B3/P8/1PP6/9/9/9 w p","Diagram 3-2")
B.akD=new A.c("You will then promote the Pawn on 6a, against which White will play G-7a, then you pull the tokin back to 5b. The Mino-castle is sure to fall.")
B.akH=new A.c("What if White plays Gx5b at Diagram 3-2? You know it. R-7a+ will lead to exactly the same position as above.")
B.aj1=new A.c("If you are thinking of playing P*5c instead of P*5b, you should remember White's P*5a will turn the table around.")
B.amZ=new A.c("When playing against the Mino-castle, attack the Gold on 6a. This is the golden rule.")
