B.afV=new A.c("Diagram 1 shows where White has just dropped a Knight on 2d. It may not seem particularly alarming, but is in fact a threatmate, starting from N*3f. Black has to prevent that, but how?")
B.af6=new A.c("N*4h? Indeed, a Knight drop can be effectively defended by a counter-drop of the same piece, sometimes. But in this case, it will allow White to continue his/her attack by P-1e. If you respond with Px1e, White's N*1f will bring a near-mate position. See for yourself that your N on 4h will only block your own King.")
B.alp=new A.c("You may come up with G*2f on Diagram 1, which will also cover the edge. Not a bad idea, but what if White plays L*2e? You cannot respond with G*2e. If you do, White will proceed to carry out the original plan: N*3f...mate.")
B.ajs=new A.c("The move to play here is S*2e.")
B.aez=new A.c("See how the Silver covers both squares the opponent's Knight threatens: 3f and 1f.")
