B.amu=new A.c("White's G*3e aims to take the Silver, but you can go on to get rid of the menacing Knight to kill the threat. Remember that a Knight at the head of the opponent's Knight not only covers both squares under threat, but also can take the Knight itself when necessary.")
B.aiL=new A.c("Do not, therefore, drop a Bishop instead of a Silver. Apparently they have a similar function, but in this case, a Bishop is helpless when White plays G*3e.")
