B.LB=new A.p("9/9/9/9/9/2PPP4/PPSG2b2/1KG3r2/LN7 b rs","Diagram 5")
B.aeI=new A.c("White will next play Rx7h, to which Black will have to respond with Kx7h. Then there will follow S*6i, Kx6i, R*4i, which will practically finish the game (Diagram 6).")
B.M0=new A.p("9/9/9/9/9/2PPP4/PPSG2b2/9/LN1K1r3 b RSg","Diagram 6")
B.anb=new A.c("From Diagram 6, Black's K-7h won't do. G*7i will end the game.")
B.afm=new A.c("Back in Diagram 5, there is one move you can play to get yourself out of danger, which is...?")
B.a3B=A.a(s(["G6g-6h"]),t.s)
B.aaB=new A.Q(null,B.a3B,B.u)
B.aml=new A.c("By placing two Golds side by side to guard your King, you can buy time. In the yagura-opening, you are supposed to place your Gold on 6g, but when you get into the endgame, the Gold had better be on 6h for the defense.")
B.adY=new A.c("I might add that S-6h instead of G6g-6h is less preferable, even if it may appear to be similar in effect. There is a well-known endgame tesuji against the Yagura: S*6i, to which S-6h is hardly well-prepared.")
B.aii=new A.c("Just remember that a Gold functions better when sitting in the back rank.")
