B.ahb=new A.c("In Diagram 3, a Silver is on 6g instead of 7h and a Gold on 7h instead of 6g. This is a little better than Diagram 2. But in view of the function of Generals, the one on the upper front should be the Silver, since it is the piece with which you act on your first offensive.")
B.ag5=new A.c("Now, we will look into how the Pawn-exchange on the 6th file will further affect the already ill-shaped formation.")
B.ae0=new A.c("From Diagram 1, you can play: P-6e, Px6e, Sx6e, P*6d, S-7f. No problem resulted from the exchange. From Diagram 3, however, if you play likewise: P-6e, Px6e, Gx6e, P*6d, G-6f, your Gold will end up blocking your own Bishop's path. You will have to play an extra move, G-7f, to fix the bad shape.")
B.amI=new A.c('As there are exceptions to every rule, "Silver on top of Gold" can work against you at times, but more often it will lead you to the right track. That\'s what the basics are all about.')
