B.a8G=new A.Q("Moves from Diagram 2-3:",B.a4c,B.u)
B.aew=new A.c("After this, Black can take a Gold on 7a.")
B.aeg=new A.c("Even if Black has no piece to drop on 8c, he can continue his offensive by Sx8e aiming for P8c+. (Diagram 2-4)")
B.Lj=new A.p("kng1+R4/lsg6/p+Pppp4/9/PSP6/3PP4/2BG5/1KG6/LN7 w 2p","Diagram 2-4")
B.akx=new A.c("See for yourself that White will eventually lose whichever piece he takes the promoted Pawn with, by Black's next move: P*8d.")
B.aiF=new A.c("Also against the Mino castle, the same tesuji is quite effective. See Diagram 2-5.")
B.Nl=new A.p("ln1g1+R3/1ks1g4/2ppp4/pP7/1pP5/P1SPP4/2BG5/1KG6/LN7 w 2p","Diagram 2-5")
B.aer=new A.c("Black, if he has any piece other than a Pawn, can drop it on 8c, likewise. If not, he can play Sx8e thereby applying a pressure on White's King. Please note that he has made his own King safer by getting rid of the Pawn on 8e, which really makes a big difference towards the end.")
B.ah9=new A.c("Remember a dangling Pawn right in front of the opponent's King never fails to work in your favor. Ask yourself if a joining Pawn tesuji makes this possible.")
