B.ach=new A.ar(B.R7)
B.ajr=new A.c("In this section, I will show you how the proverb is effective in attacking the Mino castle.")
B.Ng=new A.p("ln1g3nl/1ks1g4/pppps1b2/4pp1r1/2SP2ppp/1R1B1P3/P3PGSPP/5GK2/LN5NL b 3P","Diagram 4-1")
B.ajQ=new A.c("Diagram 4-1 (last move B3c) is from a double ranging Rook opening, where Black has developed an ideal attacking formation with the four pieces (Rook, Bishop, Silver, and Knight ) well organized against White's Mino castle.")
B.Za=A.a(s(["P*8d","Px8d","P*8c"]),t.s)
B.a9o=new A.Q("Moves from Diagram 4-1:",B.Za,B.j)
B.M8=new A.p("ln1g3nl/1ks1g4/pPpps1b2/1p2pp1r1/2SP2ppp/1R1B1P3/P3PGSPP/5GK2/LN5NL w Pp","Diagram 4-2")
B.alx=new A.c("After White's Px8d, Sx8d won't do, because White will then play P*8c.")
B.YQ=A.a(s(["Sx8c","Sx8d","Sx8d"]),t.s)
B.aab=new A.Q("Moves from Diagram 4-1:",B.YQ,B.u)
B.MN=new A.p("ln1g3nl/1k2g4/p1pps1b2/1s2pp1r1/3P2ppp/1R1B1P3/P3PGSPP/5GK2/LN5NL b 2Ps2p","Diagram 4-3")
B.ais=new A.c("If, from Diagram 4-2, White plays K7a, Black can comfortably play Rx8d. So, White's Sx8c is the best defense, and then Black goes on to play Sx8d for Silver exchange.")
B.akw=new A.c("From Diagram 4-3, Rx8d may seem natural enough, but think further. White will then play P*8c to repel the Rook, which will be no good for Black. So, here again, P*8c (Diagram 4-4) is a good move.")
B.Mx=new A.p("ln1g3nl/1k2g4/pPpps1b2/1s2pp1r1/3P2ppp/1R1B1P3/P3PGSPP/5GK2/LN5NL w Ps2p","Diagram 4-4")
B.agd=new A.c("There will follow: Kx8c, Rx8d, K7b, P*8c. The 8th file will certainly be under your control, making a winning position for you.")
